1
00:00:44,583 --> 00:00:45,875
Okay, pencils down.

2
00:00:45,958 --> 00:00:46,916
[STUDENTS sigh]

3
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:48,541
[chattering]

4
00:00:48,625 --> 00:00:51,708
[RYOUKO] Only one more day
of exams. You can make it!

5
00:00:52,833 --> 00:00:53,583
[MIU]
How'd you do?

6
00:00:53,666 --> 00:00:55,125
[SETSUKO]
Terrible.

7
00:00:55,208 --> 00:00:56,750
[AIRA]
Wanna go with us, Akane?

8
00:00:56,833 --> 00:00:57,916
--[AKANE] Huh?
--[AIRA] Come on.

9
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,500
We're shopping
for the school trip.

10
00:00:59,583 --> 00:01:00,791
[AIRA]
It's coming up soon.

11
00:01:00,875 --> 00:01:03,208
Sorry, but I have
practice today.

12
00:01:03,291 --> 00:01:04,208
Too bad.

13
00:01:04,291 --> 00:01:05,291
Tomorrow's test
is language arts?

14
00:01:05,375 --> 00:01:06,708
[AIRA]
I hope it's not hard.

15
00:01:12,541 --> 00:01:13,708
[ROMAN]
Kota!

16
00:01:13,791 --> 00:01:16,208
Hey, come on, why do you
look so depressed, man?

17
00:01:16,291 --> 00:01:17,416
Uh-oh, did you fail?

18
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:18,833
Fail is a strong word.

19
00:01:18,916 --> 00:01:20,833
Yeah, meaning
it's the right word.

20
00:01:20,916 --> 00:01:21,958
Wanna see my new move?

21
00:01:22,041 --> 00:01:22,791
[KOTAROU]
Not really.

22
00:01:22,875 --> 00:01:24,916
[DAICHI]
Ogasawara Dynamic!

23
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,750
[KOTAROU]
Stop! Let go!

24
00:01:26,833 --> 00:01:28,208
Fine, take this!

25
00:01:28,291 --> 00:01:29,875
Jeez! That hurt!

26
00:01:29,958 --> 00:01:31,291
To be fair,
I did ask you to stop.

27
00:01:31,375 --> 00:01:32,750
I thought you said
it was a new move.

28
00:01:32,833 --> 00:01:33,958
[DAICHI]
It is!

29
00:03:49,166 --> 00:03:49,958
[SHIGE]
Hm?

30
00:03:50,041 --> 00:03:51,541
Well, good morning!

31
00:03:51,625 --> 00:03:53,541
You're here early.
What about school?

32
00:03:53,625 --> 00:03:56,041
Uh, it's an exam day.

33
00:03:56,125 --> 00:03:57,500
[SHIGE laughs]

34
00:03:57,583 --> 00:03:59,041
Sounds exciting.

35
00:03:59,125 --> 00:04:00,875
[KOTAROU] You're up
pretty early yourself.

36
00:04:00,958 --> 00:04:03,000
Yes, we're cleaning
up Kagura Hall.

37
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:10,708
Good morning, Kotarou.

38
00:04:12,041 --> 00:04:14,708
You're here early. No school?

39
00:04:14,791 --> 00:04:16,208
[KOTAROU]
I-It's exam week.

40
00:04:18,791 --> 00:04:21,458
[DAISUKE]
Uh... Is that about your book?

41
00:04:21,541 --> 00:04:23,458
The one you let me
look at recently?

42
00:04:25,083 --> 00:04:29,875
You read my second story,
but this was about my first one.

43
00:04:29,958 --> 00:04:31,750
[SHIGE]
Hey Kotarou!

44
00:04:31,833 --> 00:04:34,875
We're looking forward to seeing
you on Sunday. For practice?

45
00:04:34,958 --> 00:04:36,833
[KOTAROU]
Uh, yep!

46
00:04:36,916 --> 00:04:39,458
So then you've submitted
an entry before?

47
00:04:39,541 --> 00:04:40,791
What did they say?

48
00:04:44,875 --> 00:04:46,750
Must be hard to
focus on school.

49
00:04:55,291 --> 00:04:56,958
[JUNKO]
Kotarou!

50
00:04:57,041 --> 00:04:59,583
You had better be studying
up there, young man!

51
00:04:59,666 --> 00:05:00,750
[KOTAROU]
I am!

52
00:05:04,791 --> 00:05:06,375
I'm trying to, at least.

53
00:05:17,541 --> 00:05:19,708
Is that too weird?

54
00:05:28,583 --> 00:05:29,541
[phone chimes]

55
00:05:46,208 --> 00:05:47,833
Akane, did you take your bath?

56
00:05:47,916 --> 00:05:49,458
[AKANE]
Oh, yeah, a while ago.

57
00:05:49,541 --> 00:05:50,541
Okay.

58
00:05:50,625 --> 00:05:52,083
Well, I guess I'll
go take one, then.

59
00:06:09,458 --> 00:06:10,916
[KOTAROU]
What's wrong with me.

60
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,708
Why can't I talk to her
this easily at school?

61
00:06:13,791 --> 00:06:14,750
[phone chimes]

62
00:06:51,083 --> 00:06:52,041
[phone chimes]

63
00:06:54,833 --> 00:06:58,000
[KOTAROU laughing]

64
00:07:08,083 --> 00:07:09,625
[RYOUKO]
Right, pencils down!

65
00:07:09,708 --> 00:07:11,791
Please pass your papers forward.

66
00:07:24,708 --> 00:07:25,833
[ROMAN]
Kota!

67
00:07:25,916 --> 00:07:27,625
Wanna hang out
after school today?

68
00:07:27,708 --> 00:07:29,250
Nah, I have to go to my club.

69
00:07:29,333 --> 00:07:31,083
--[ROMAN] Aww...
--I have club today, too.

70
00:07:31,166 --> 00:07:32,166
[ROMAN]
Seriously?

71
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:34,583
You guys are so lame.

72
00:07:34,666 --> 00:07:37,125
Come on, let's go
do something fun.

73
00:07:37,208 --> 00:07:39,125
[DAICHI] We're not here
to entertain you, man.

74
00:07:39,208 --> 00:07:41,458
[ROMAN]
We never hang out anymore.

75
00:07:41,541 --> 00:07:42,750
[MIU]
Bye, Akane!

76
00:07:42,833 --> 00:07:43,666
See ya!

77
00:07:43,750 --> 00:07:45,166
Have a good one.

78
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:47,041
[AKANE]
Uh, yeah. See ya!

79
00:07:47,666 --> 00:07:48,583
[DAICHI]
I guess that sounds fun.

80
00:07:48,666 --> 00:07:50,125
[ROMAN]
And we'll hit the arcade!

81
00:07:50,208 --> 00:07:51,291
Just skip out on your club.

82
00:07:51,375 --> 00:07:52,791
I can't! I've skipped
too much as it is!

83
00:07:52,875 --> 00:07:54,291
[ROMAN]
Come on, it's just one day.

84
00:07:54,375 --> 00:07:55,583
[DAICHI]
I'll get in trouble!

85
00:07:59,958 --> 00:08:01,541
I'm so excited to run today.

86
00:08:01,625 --> 00:08:02,583
Yeah!

87
00:08:03,875 --> 00:08:05,041
Hold on.

88
00:08:05,125 --> 00:08:06,708
I'm just gonna go throw
this away real quick.

89
00:08:06,791 --> 00:08:07,750
'Kay.

90
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,583
[CHINATSU]
Hey!

91
00:08:12,666 --> 00:08:14,375
What's up, Curly- <i>kun</i> ?

92
00:08:14,458 --> 00:08:15,875
Hi!

93
00:08:22,583 --> 00:08:25,125
Oh, he and I
are friends now.

94
00:08:25,208 --> 00:08:27,041
Thanks to you,
because you told me

95
00:08:27,125 --> 00:08:28,750
he was really cool.

96
00:08:33,333 --> 00:08:36,041
The meet in is one week,
so do your best!

97
00:08:36,125 --> 00:08:37,083
[GROUP]
Right!

98
00:08:51,083 --> 00:08:52,833
[AOI] Have you noticed
all the hook-ups?

99
00:08:52,916 --> 00:08:54,250
[CHINATSU]
Like, everyone's in love.

100
00:08:54,333 --> 00:08:55,583
[AOI]
It's 'cause of the school trip.

101
00:08:55,666 --> 00:08:56,666
[AKANE]
That's just silly.

102
00:08:56,750 --> 00:08:57,500
[AOI]
I know, right?

103
00:08:57,583 --> 00:08:58,958
Huh? No, it isn't.

104
00:08:59,041 --> 00:09:01,375
A boyfriend would
be awesome, right?

105
00:09:01,458 --> 00:09:02,750
I think I'm good, actually.

106
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:04,291
Not even Hira?

107
00:09:04,375 --> 00:09:06,166
--[HIRA] What's that?
--[AOI] Nothing, nosy!

108
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:07,166
[CHINATSU]
You two should date!

109
00:09:07,250 --> 00:09:08,666
What, why?

110
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:10,083
[CHINATSU] I heard a girl
asked him out but he said no.

111
00:09:10,166 --> 00:09:11,750
--Why, though?
--There's someone he likes.

112
00:09:11,833 --> 00:09:12,958
[AOI]
Definitely Akane.

113
00:09:13,041 --> 00:09:14,625
[CHINATSU]
That's what I think, too!

114
00:09:20,125 --> 00:09:21,000
Man, I bombed.

115
00:09:21,083 --> 00:09:22,333
Those tests were pretty hard.

116
00:09:22,416 --> 00:09:23,958
How'd you do?

117
00:09:24,041 --> 00:09:26,291
[KOTAROU] The literature club
has this superstition.

118
00:09:29,791 --> 00:09:31,625
[KOTAROU]
Pick out a random book.

119
00:09:31,708 --> 00:09:35,583
Whatever your situation is,
the pages inside

120
00:09:35,666 --> 00:09:37,416
will have the perfect advice.

121
00:09:46,958 --> 00:09:47,916
That's it.

122
00:10:04,416 --> 00:10:05,458
Fine.

123
00:10:12,291 --> 00:10:13,875
[CHINATSU]
He should just ask her out.

124
00:10:13,958 --> 00:10:15,083
Hira?

125
00:10:15,166 --> 00:10:16,625
[CHINATSU] I'm positive
Akane would say yes.

126
00:10:16,708 --> 00:10:19,541
He'd better not
before the track meet.

127
00:10:19,625 --> 00:10:21,875
[CHINATSU] After it's over then,
when emotions are high!

128
00:10:21,958 --> 00:10:23,708
[AOI]
Yeah, that might work.

129
00:10:28,291 --> 00:10:30,291
Um, have you chosen
a high school yet?

130
00:10:32,166 --> 00:10:33,666
Oh, yeah, more or less.

131
00:10:33,750 --> 00:10:35,916
Don't they usually
ask you after midterms?

132
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,375
I've just been focusing
on the track meet for now.

133
00:10:38,458 --> 00:10:39,708
Oh, that's right.

134
00:10:39,791 --> 00:10:41,791
Don't you worry, sweetie,
Mom and I will come--

135
00:10:41,875 --> 00:10:44,041
Why don't you go to
your sister's school?

136
00:10:44,125 --> 00:10:45,875
Hey, yeah, my school's awesome.

137
00:10:45,958 --> 00:10:47,416
Oh, really?

138
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:50,000
You'd like it. They're like
super club-oriented or whatever.

139
00:10:50,083 --> 00:10:51,708
I think it'd be good for you.

140
00:10:51,791 --> 00:10:53,041
[AKANE]
Hmm...

141
00:10:53,125 --> 00:10:54,583
But it's so far away.

142
00:10:54,666 --> 00:10:56,833
So then why don't we
move back to Tokyo?

143
00:10:56,916 --> 00:10:59,333
Knowing Dad, he'll probably just
get transferred again anyway.

144
00:10:59,416 --> 00:11:00,833
Way to have faith in me, dear.

145
00:11:00,916 --> 00:11:02,875
Come on, it'd be
super convenient for me.

146
00:11:02,958 --> 00:11:04,250
Can I have seconds?

147
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:16,583
[starting pistol fires]

148
00:11:16,666 --> 00:11:19,041
Go, go! Let's go,
let's go, Akane! Go, go!

149
00:11:19,125 --> 00:11:20,750
Let's go, let's go, Akane!

150
00:11:20,833 --> 00:11:22,791
[CHINATSU] Let's go,
let's go, go go, Akane!

151
00:11:22,875 --> 00:11:24,833
[TRACK TEAM] Let's go,
let's go, go go, Akane!

152
00:11:24,916 --> 00:11:26,333
[CHINATSU]
You can do it! Akane!

153
00:11:32,666 --> 00:11:35,375
[CROWD clapping]

154
00:11:35,458 --> 00:11:37,208
Great job...

155
00:11:37,291 --> 00:11:39,958
Akane!

156
00:11:40,041 --> 00:11:41,666
Great job...

157
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:43,625
Akane!

158
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:01,541
[CHINATSU]
I won't give up.

159
00:12:18,541 --> 00:12:21,500
[TV 3A] The baby giraffe was
debuted to the public today.

160
00:12:21,583 --> 00:12:23,416
Needless to say,
the adorable critter

161
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:26,000
has captured zoo-goers hearts.

162
00:12:26,083 --> 00:12:27,416
The zoo-keepers say...

163
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:30,083
I noticed you're on LINE
an awful lot lately.

164
00:12:30,166 --> 00:12:31,750
Mind your own business.

165
00:12:32,375 --> 00:12:34,875
[TV 3A] Tomorrow will be partly
cloudy with a small chance--

166
00:12:37,666 --> 00:12:40,708
Aww... The same day
as my practice.

167
00:12:54,208 --> 00:12:55,541
[CHINATSU]
He should just ask her out.

168
00:12:55,625 --> 00:12:56,750
Hira?

169
00:12:56,833 --> 00:12:58,833
[CHINATSU] I'm positive
Akane would say yes.

170
00:13:05,916 --> 00:13:07,666
Ah, jeez...

171
00:13:07,750 --> 00:13:09,708
I wanna ask, but should I?

172
00:13:09,791 --> 00:13:12,541
Come on! Think already!

173
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:16,958
[phone chimes]

174
00:13:21,875 --> 00:13:22,833
[chuckles]

175
00:13:30,458 --> 00:13:31,416
[phone chimes]

176
00:13:35,416 --> 00:13:37,416
[KOTAROU]
Okay, let's do this.

177
00:13:56,750 --> 00:13:57,708
[starting pistol fires]

178
00:14:01,166 --> 00:14:03,166
[ANNOUNCER 3A] The winner of the
last race was the participant

179
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:04,500
in lane six.

180
00:14:04,583 --> 00:14:06,375
Miss Kimura from Jounan.

181
00:14:06,458 --> 00:14:09,708
Her winning record is 14.21
seconds with a tailwind

182
00:14:09,791 --> 00:14:12,083
of 1.3 meters per second.

183
00:14:30,291 --> 00:14:31,333
Are you okay?

184
00:14:32,541 --> 00:14:33,500
[AKANE]
Yeah.

185
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,708
Do you think you'll
beat your own record?

186
00:14:39,125 --> 00:14:40,166
[AKANE]
I don't know.

187
00:14:42,125 --> 00:14:43,458
I bet you will.

188
00:14:43,541 --> 00:14:46,041
I mean, you have been
working really hard for this.

189
00:14:48,541 --> 00:14:49,541
[AKANE]
Mm-hmm.

190
00:14:49,625 --> 00:14:51,333
Let's do our best out there.

191
00:14:52,625 --> 00:14:53,583
[AKANE]
Yeah.

192
00:14:55,166 --> 00:14:55,958
[HIRA]
Hey...

193
00:14:56,041 --> 00:14:57,000
[AKANE]
Hm?

194
00:15:06,541 --> 00:15:08,333
Um, uh, Mizuno?

195
00:15:09,291 --> 00:15:10,458
Come on! Let's go!

196
00:15:14,333 --> 00:15:16,500
Ah, forget about it. Bye!

197
00:15:20,125 --> 00:15:21,250
[CHINATSU]
Oh, Hira.

198
00:15:21,333 --> 00:15:22,916
[HIRA] Hey, I'll be
cheering for you guys!

199
00:15:29,541 --> 00:15:30,583
Here we go.

200
00:16:18,166 --> 00:16:19,958
Oh, boy, Akane looks nervous.

201
00:16:20,041 --> 00:16:22,291
Akane! Go get 'em!

202
00:16:22,375 --> 00:16:23,625
Let's go!

203
00:17:05,125 --> 00:17:06,083
[STARTER 3A]
Set!

204
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:08,541
[starting pistol fires]

205
00:17:09,833 --> 00:17:11,458
[ANNOUNCER 3A]
Lane five takes the lead.

206
00:17:11,541 --> 00:17:12,750
It's Akane Mizuno!

207
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:14,000
Come on!

208
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:24,791
[taiko drums playing]

209
00:17:50,791 --> 00:17:52,208
[KOTAROU]
I wonder how it went.

210
00:17:53,625 --> 00:17:54,958
[cash register beeping]

211
00:17:55,041 --> 00:17:57,125
[TRACK TEAM 3G]
Ugh. This line sucks.

212
00:17:57,916 --> 00:17:58,750
[TRACK TEAM 3C]
I know what I'm getting!

213
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:00,333
Think I'll get the large shake.

214
00:18:00,416 --> 00:18:02,125
Hey, where you'd
get so much money?

215
00:18:02,208 --> 00:18:03,916
[AOI] My parents gave it
to me as a reward.

216
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:05,250
[CHINATSU]
No fair.

217
00:18:05,958 --> 00:18:07,000
You hungry?

218
00:18:08,041 --> 00:18:10,791
[AKANE]
Uh, definitely.

219
00:18:10,875 --> 00:18:13,750
[taiko drums playing]

220
00:18:22,416 --> 00:18:23,750
[HIRA]
Did you see that one girl run?

221
00:18:23,833 --> 00:18:24,750
[TRACK TEAM 3C]
Which one?

222
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:25,583
[HIRA]
The one in the third lane.

223
00:18:25,666 --> 00:18:26,208
[TRACK TEAM 3G]
Oh, yeah!

224
00:18:26,291 --> 00:18:27,541
She was fast.

225
00:18:27,625 --> 00:18:28,833
I've made up my mind.

226
00:18:28,916 --> 00:18:30,083
I'm gonna train harder!

227
00:18:30,166 --> 00:18:31,583
--[AOI] Oh?
--Seriously!

228
00:18:31,666 --> 00:18:32,791
What about the school trip?

229
00:18:32,875 --> 00:18:33,875
Uh...

230
00:18:33,958 --> 00:18:35,166
[AOI] Are you gonna
train in Kyoto?

231
00:18:35,250 --> 00:18:36,916
--[CHINATSU] Maybe I will!
--[AOI] Yeah, right.

232
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:39,750
[laughing]

233
00:18:39,833 --> 00:18:40,875
Hey, did you guys hear?

234
00:18:40,958 --> 00:18:42,750
I heard Tsubasa asked Aira out.

235
00:18:42,833 --> 00:18:44,041
Aw, jeez, really?

236
00:18:44,125 --> 00:18:46,000
Aren't they in
your class, Akane?

237
00:18:46,083 --> 00:18:47,416
[AKANE]
Uh, what?

238
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:48,666
Who are we talking about?

239
00:18:48,750 --> 00:18:50,208
--What happened?
--[CHINATSU] This is girl talk!

240
00:18:50,291 --> 00:18:51,541
No boys allowed.

241
00:18:56,958 --> 00:18:57,833
Hey, what's wrong?

242
00:18:57,916 --> 00:18:59,458
Uh, bathroom break.

243
00:19:00,791 --> 00:19:02,750
[faint taiko drums]

244
00:19:08,708 --> 00:19:09,666
[KOTAROU sighs]

245
00:19:18,166 --> 00:19:19,916
[GIRL 3B]
Thank you for today!

246
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,500
[ALL]
Thank you for today!

247
00:19:21,583 --> 00:19:24,000
Right! Really nice
work, everyone.

248
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:31,375
See ya later.

249
00:19:45,666 --> 00:19:47,375
[KOTAROU]
Mizuno, hi.

250
00:19:47,458 --> 00:19:49,208
Oh, hello.

251
00:19:55,166 --> 00:19:56,333
Come on. This way.

252
00:19:56,416 --> 00:19:57,875
[AKANE]
Uh... Mm-hmm.

253
00:20:19,583 --> 00:20:21,333
